description: Visualize PMI metrics data for your WebSphere Application Server

panels.description: Displays the "recent CPU usage" for the Java Virtual Machine processes.
panels.title: Process CPU Usage

panels.description: The average CPU utilization since the last query. The System CPU load metric value is only available from the nodeagent server from each node.
panels.title: System CPU Usage

panels.description: Shows the Heap Usage in graph format.
panels.title: Heap Usage (Percentage)

panels.description: Shows the Heap Usage in graph format in table format.
panels.title: Heap Usage (Percentage)

panels.description: The current Heap used by the jvms
panels.title: Heap Usage (Bytes)

panels.description: Shows the Heap Usage in table format.
panels.title: Heap Usage (Bytes)

panels.description: Instances with an increase in heap usage within the last ${dur}.
panels.title: Increasing Heap Usage Trend Based on Last ${dur}

panels.description: Instances projected to reach the max heap size within [$maxHeapUsageProjection hour(s)] based on  data over the last [[dur]].
panels.title: Servers That May Reach Max Heap Usage Within [$maxHeapUsageProjection hour(s)] Based on Last [[dur]]

panels.description: An instance's maximum heap size. This value is based on the Xmx value set on admin console for the JVM.
panels.title: Maximum Heap Size

panels.description: The average response time for requests made to a particular servlet based on data over the last [[dur]].

targets.expr: avg(rate(was_servlet_response_time_seconds_total{instance=~"[[instance]]", node=~"[[node]]", server=~"[[server]]", appname=~"[[appname]]"}[[dur]]) / rate(was_servlet_requests_total{instance=~"[[instance]]", node=~"[[node]]", server=~"[[server]]", appname=~"[[appname]]"}[[dur]])) by (servlet, instance, appname) > 0

panels.title: Slowest Servlets Over Last [[dur]] by Average Response Time

panels.description: The number of visits made to a servlet instance within the past [[dur]].

targets.expr: sum(increase(was_servlet_requests_total{instance=~"[[instance]]", node=~"[[node]]", server=~"[[server]]", appname=~"[[appname]]"}[[dur]])) by (servlet, instance, node, server, appname)

panels.title: Servlet Request Count Over Last [[dur]]

panels.description: The average response time for a request made to a servlet based on data over the last [[dur]].

targets.expr: rate(was_servlet_response_time_seconds_total{instance=~"[[instance]]", node=~"[[node]]", server=~"[[server]]", appname=~"[[appname]]"}[[dur]]) / rate(was_servlet_requests_total{instance=~"[[instance]]", node=~"[[node]]", server=~"[[server]]", appname=~"[[appname]]"}[[dur]])

panels.title: Average Response Time per Servlet Request Over Last [[dur]]

panels.description: The sum of visits to a particular servlet over all servers across nodes and instances based on data over the last [[dur]].
panels.title: Request Count by Servlet Over Last [[dur]]

panels.description: The average response time for requests made to a particular servlet, across all servers nodes and instances based on data over the last [[dur]].

targets.expr: avg(rate(was_servlet_response_time_seconds_total{instance=~"[[instance]]", node=~"[[node]]", server=~"[[server]]", appname=~"[[appname]]"}[[dur]]) / rate(was_servlet_requests_total{instance=~"[[instance]]", node=~"[[node]]", server=~"[[server]]", appname=~"[[appname]]"}[[dur]])) by (servlet, appname)

panels.title: Average Response Time per Request Over Last [[dur]] By Servlet

panels.description: The average response time for an EJB based on data over the last [[dur]].

targets.expr: avg(rate(was_ejb_response_time_seconds_total{instance=~"[[instance]]", node=~"[[node]]", server=~"[[server]]"}[[dur]]) / rate(was_ejb_responses_total{instance=~"[[instance]]", node=~"[[node]]", server=~"[[server]]"}[[dur]])) by (ejb, instance)

panels.title: Average Response Time per EJB Over Last [[dur]]

panels.description: Table that lists the slowest EJBs over the last [[dur]].

targets.expr: avg(rate(was_ejb_response_time_seconds_total{instance=~"[[instance]]", node=~"[[node]]", server=~"[[server]]"}[[dur]]) / rate(was_ejb_responses_total{instance=~"[[instance]]", node=~"[[node]]", server=~"[[server]]"}[[dur]])) by (instance, ejb) > 0

panels.title: Slowest EJBs Over Last [[dur]] by Average Response Time

panels.description: The total number of connection requests that were used over the last [[dur]]. Any connections that are currently in use are not included in this total.
panels.title: Connections Used Over Last [[dur]]

panels.description: The total number of connection requests that waited for a connection because of a full connection pool over the last [[dur]].
panels.title: Connection Requests Queued Over Last [[dur]]

panels.description: The average time any used connection was put in use, based on data over the last ${dur}.
panels.title: Average Time Usage per Connection Over Last ${dur}

panels.description: The average wait time for any queued connection request, based on data over the last ${dur}.
panels.title: Average Wait Time per Queued Connection Request Over Last ${dur}

panels.description: The sum of managed connections in the free, shared, and unshared pools.
panels.title: Managed Connections

panels.description: The number of free connections in the pool.
panels.title: Free Connections

panels.description: The number of connections that are in use.
panels.title: Connection Handles

panels.description: The total number of managed connections created in the past [[dur]]
panels.title: Connections created in the past [[dur]]

panels.description: The total number of managed connections destroyed since the pool was created.
panels.title: Connections Destroyed in the past [[dur]]

panels.description: The total amount of message data (in bytes) written in the past [[dur]] from the messaging engines.
panels.title: Message Data (in bytes) Written in the past [[dur]] from the Messaging Engines

panels.description: The total amount of message data (in bytes) read in the past [[dur]] from the messaging engines.
panels.title: Message Data (in bytes) Read in the past [[dur]] from the Message Engines

panels.description: The total amount of message data (in bytes) written in the past [[dur]] from the Clients
panels.title: Message Data (in bytes) Written in the past [[dur]] from the Clients

panels.description: The total amount of message data (in bytes) read in the past [[dur]] from the Clients
panels.title: Message Data (in bytes) Read in the past [[dur]] from the Clients

panels.description: Messages Produced by Queue in the last [[dur]]
panels.title: Messages Produced by Queue in the last [[dur]]

panels.description: Messages Consumed by Queue in the last [[dur]]
panels.title: Messages Consumed by Queue in the last [[dur]]

panels.description: A session is considered active if the application server is processing a request that uses that user session.
panels.title: Active Sessions

panels.description: A session is considered live if the session is loaded into memory by the application server.
panels.title: Live  Sessions

panels.description: The number of sessions that were invalidated.
panels.title: Invalidated Sessions in the past [[dur]]

panels.description: Created sessions in the last [[dur]]
panels.title: Created Sessions in the past [[dur]]

panels.description: The size of the thread pools in each server, based on data over the last [[dur]].
panels.title: Largest Thread Pool Sizes Over Last [[dur]]

panels.description: The number of threads that are actively running tasks.
panels.title: Active Threads

panels.description: The size of the thread pool in each server.
panels.title: Thread Pool Size

panels.description: The number of threads declared hung in the last [[dur]]
panels.title: Declared Hung Threads in the past [[dur]]

panels.description: The number of concurrent hung threads
panels.title: Concurrent Hung Threads

panels.description: A table reporting the portion of time a specific server has spent Garbage Collecting in the last [[dur]].
panels.title: Time Spent Garbage Collecting During Last [[dur]]

panels.description: The average time a server took on garbage collection, based on data over the last [[dur]].
panels.title: Time per Garbage Collection Cycle [[dur]] moving average

panels.description: The time elapsed since the start of the JVM.
panels.title: JVM Uptime
